  {title:'Google May 2026 Core Update Completes — Biggest Ranking Shift of the Year',tier:'s',tierLabel:'S Tier',pipeline:'SEO → Content Strategy',source:'Search Engine Land',url:'https://searchengineland.com/google-may-2026-core-update-rolling-out-now-478430',benefit:'Google\'s biggest algorithm update of the year finished June 2 — check every client\'s traffic in Google now and act before any client calls you about dropped rankings.',roi:'Immediate',fit:5,why:'The May 2026 Core Update ran 11 days 21 hours and SEO practitioners called it significantly more impactful than the March update. LCP now has a firm 2-second good threshold and all three Core Web Vitals are scored holistically — failing one compounds the penalty for all three. June 9 is the first clean comparison window in Search Console.',steps:['Pull organic traffic in Google Search Console for all clients — compare May 21–June 2 vs the same period in April.','For any site showing drops, run PageSpeed Insights and identify which CWV metric is failing the new thresholds.','Prioritise hero image AVIF conversion and `fetchpriority="high"` on the worst-performing client sites — fastest LCP gain available.'],impl:{Research:'1h',Build:'—',QA:'3h',Rollout:'4h',Total:'8h / site'},impact:{'Build Speed':{val:'—',neutral:true},'QA Pass Rate':{val:'—',neutral:true},'Page Perf':{val:'+20%'}},compat:{Webflow:'Yes',Figma:'No',n8n:'Yes',Cloudflare:'Yes',Playwright:'No','Website QA':'Yes'}},
  {title:'Webflow Pricing Restructure Live — AI Credit Enforcement Starts June 29',tier:'s',tierLabel:'S Tier',pipeline:'Webflow Build → Client Handoff',source:'Webflow Blog',url:'https://webflow.com/blog/simplified-plans-and-updated-pricing-2026',benefit:'Webflow starts blocking AI features for clients who exceed their credit limits on June 29 — review all client plans this week so no one gets an unexpected outage.',roi:'Immediate',fit:5,why:'As of May 13 the old CMS ($23/mo) and Business ($39/mo) site plans merged into a Premium Site plan ($25/mo annual). CMS item limits doubled to 20,000. AI credits are included in all Workspace plans from May 13 but enforcement — meaning usage gets blocked if you exceed allowance — starts June 29. Any client using Webflow AI features needs to be on the right plan before that date.',steps:['Audit every client site plan in Webflow — map each to the new pricing using the Webflow pricing calculator.','Flag any client site using Webflow AI features — calculate their credit usage and confirm they are on a plan with sufficient allowance.','Contact clients who will see a price change at next renewal this week — proactive communication prevents surprises.'],impl:{Research:'2h',Build:'—',QA:'—',Rollout:'2h',Total:'4h'},impact:{'Build Speed':{val:'—',neutral:true},'QA Pass Rate':{val:'—',neutral:true},'Page Perf':{val:'—',neutral:true}},compat:{Webflow:'Yes',Figma:'No',n8n:'No',Cloudflare:'No',Playwright:'No','Website QA':'No'}},
  {title:'React 19.2.7 + Next.js 16.2.7 — FormData Regression Patch (June 1)',tier:'a',tierLabel:'A Tier',pipeline:'Webflow Build (Headless Only)',source:'React GitHub',url:'https://github.com/facebook/react/releases',benefit:'If you have any Next.js client sites with contact forms, they may have been silently losing submitted data for weeks — patch now and check CRM records for incomplete entries.',roi:'Immediate',fit:3,why:'React 19.2.6 introduced a bug where FormData entries were silently dropped in Server Actions. Any headless Next.js site with server-side form handling deployed between 19.2.6 and June 1 may have incomplete form submission data in the client\'s CRM. React 19.2.7 and Next.js 16.2.7 both ship the fix.',steps:['Identify any headless Next.js projects using Server Actions for form handling — check deployment date against the 19.2.6 release.','Upgrade to React 19.2.7 + Next.js 16.2.7 and redeploy immediately.','Check form submission records in the client CRM for the affected period — missing fields appear as empty strings.'],impl:{Research:'0.5h',Build:'0.5h',QA:'1h',Rollout:'0.5h',Total:'2.5h'},impact:{'Build Speed':{val:'—',neutral:true},'QA Pass Rate':{val:'+10%'},'Page Perf':{val:'—',neutral:true}},compat:{Webflow:'No',Figma:'No',n8n:'Partial',Cloudflare:'Yes',Playwright:'Yes','Website QA':'No'}},
  {title:'Chrome 149 Stable Ships — CSS Gap Decorations + bfcache WebSocket Fix',tier:'a',tierLabel:'A Tier',pipeline:'Webflow Build → QA',source:'Chrome for Developers',url:'https://developer.chrome.com/blog/new-in-chrome-149',benefit:'A new CSS approach to grid spacing means your developers can skip a common workaround — less custom code to write and maintain across every client site going forward.',roi:'High',fit:4,why:'CSS gap decorations (Chrome 149 stable, June 2) let you style the spaces between grid and flex items with `column-rule-inset` and `row-rule-inset`. Until now this required negative margins or pseudo-elements — both fragile in Webflow. Also ships: `shape-outside: path()` for text-wrapping around complex shapes, and bfcache support for WebSocket pages.',steps:['Audit the shared component library for grid dividers using negative margins or pseudo-elements — replace with gap decorations.','Add the gap decoration pattern to the Webflow dev guide as the new standard for layout dividers.','Gate with `@supports (column-rule-inset: 0)` until Firefox and Safari ship support.'],impl:{Research:'0.5h',Build:'2h',QA:'1h',Rollout:'0.5h',Total:'4h'},impact:{'Build Speed':{val:'+10%'},'QA Pass Rate':{val:'+5%'},'Page Perf':{val:'+5%'}},compat:{Webflow:'Partial',Figma:'No',n8n:'No',Cloudflare:'No',Playwright:'Yes','Website QA':'Yes'}},
  {title:'Webflow AEO — Measure How Clients Appear in AI Search Answers',tier:'b',tierLabel:'B Tier',pipeline:'SEO → Content Strategy',source:'Webflow Updates',url:'https://webflow.com/feature/aeo',benefit:'Webflow now shows whether your clients appear in AI search results like ChatGPT — you can offer AI search visibility audits as a new SEO retainer service right now.',roi:'Medium',fit:4,why:'Webflow AEO (Answer Engine Optimisation) measures how a client\'s brand appears in AI search answers and generates prioritised schema, alt text, and content recommendations. Clients are already asking why they don\'t appear in AI answers — this gives you a structured tool and a repeatable audit deliverable to answer that question.',steps:['Enable Webflow AEO on the agency\'s own site first — generate an initial AI search visibility baseline to reference in pitches.','Identify which existing SEO retainer clients are on Team or Enterprise Workspace plans — they can access AEO immediately.','Build a one-page AEO Audit deliverable template: AI search visibility score, top gaps, and 3 schema recommendations.'],impl:{Research:'1h',Build:'2h',QA:'1h',Rollout:'2h',Total:'6h'},impact:{'Build Speed':{val:'—',neutral:true},'QA Pass Rate':{val:'—',neutral:true},'Page Perf':{val:'+10%'}},compat:{Webflow:'Yes',Figma:'No',n8n:'Yes',Cloudflare:'No',Playwright:'No','Website QA':'Yes'}},
  {title:'Webflow Changelog Attribution — Tracks Whether Changes Were Made by AI or Human',tier:'b',tierLabel:'B Tier',pipeline:'Webflow Build → Client Handoff',source:'Webflow Updates',url:'https://webflow.com/updates',benefit:'Webflow now records whether each site change was made by a human or AI — gives compliance-conscious clients an audit trail and builds trust in AI-assisted builds.',roi:'Medium',fit:4,why:'From June 1, Webflow\'s changelog panel attributes every change to its source: human editor, Webflow AI, or a connected MCP tool. For agencies managing AI-assisted client sites, this provides an audit trail that previously required manual documentation — particularly valuable for compliance-sensitive clients.',steps:['Review the changelog attribution on any client site that uses Webflow AI — confirm AI-generated changes have been human-reviewed before going live.','Add "review AI changelog entries" to the QA checklist for clients on AI-enabled Workspace plans.','Show the attribution panel to clients as a trust signal — it demonstrates full visibility into how their site is being edited.'],impl:{Research:'0.5h',Build:'—',QA:'0.5h',Rollout:'—',Total:'1h'},impact:{'Build Speed':{val:'—',neutral:true},'QA Pass Rate':{val:'+10%'},'Page Perf':{val:'—',neutral:true}},compat:{Webflow:'Yes',Figma:'No',n8n:'No',Cloudflare:'No',Playwright:'No','Website QA':'Yes'}},
  {title:'Chrome Prompt API Stable — On-Device AI Without a Backend or API Key',tier:'a',tierLabel:'A Tier',pipeline:'10-Template → Client Handoff',source:'Chrome for Developers',url:'https://developer.chrome.com/blog/new-in-chrome-io26',benefit:'You can now add AI features to client websites at zero backend cost — the AI runs directly in the visitor\'s browser with no server setup or API keys required.',roi:'High',fit:3,why:'The Prompt API, confirmed stable at Google I/O 2026, gives web pages direct access to Gemini Nano running locally on the device. AI text generation, summarisation, and image analysis with no server round-trip, no API billing, and no privacy risk. A new category of lightweight AI feature viable for Webflow and Next.js client builds.',steps:['Build a 2h prototype using the Prompt API — a FAQ chatbot or page summariser on a Webflow or Next.js site.','Identify 2-3 existing clients where an on-device AI assist (form helper, search, FAQ) would add value at no API cost.','Implement as progressive enhancement — feature-detect Prompt API availability before showing the AI UI.'],impl:{Research:'2h',Build:'4h',QA:'2h',Rollout:'1h',Total:'9h'},impact:{'Build Speed':{val:'+15%'},'QA Pass Rate':{val:'+5%'},'Page Perf':{val:'+5%'}},compat:{Webflow:'Partial',Figma:'No',n8n:'No',Cloudflare:'No',Playwright:'Yes','Website QA':'No'}}
